# Diagrams: ASCII art only

When a diagram clarifies a flow, architecture, or sequence, draw it as plain
ASCII art inside an ordinary fenced code block. Do **NOT** use a ```mermaid
fence — this terminal environment does not render mermaid reliably (it flashes
the diagram, then collapses it back to raw source, and the Ctrl+O toggle does
not help).

Rules:

- Use a plain triple-backtick fence (no language, or `text`). Never ```mermaid.
- Draw nodes and edges with ASCII characters: `[Box]`, `-->`, `|`, `v`, `+---+`.
- Keep labels short and in English; long or Cyrillic labels wrap badly.
- Keep it compact; prefer left-to-right or top-down. Split large flows.
- One diagram per concept.

Example:

```
[PR] --> [review] --> [worker fixes] --> [merge]
                |
                v
           [findings]
```
